i vi thuc tnh occupation v native-country, ti quyt nh d on gi tr nhng gi tr b thiu da vo mt s ct bit v s lng gi tr b thiu nhiu. Vic d on ny da trn cc thuc tnh c mi quan h gn gi vi occupation v native-country, chng hn nh education, workclass, age, v hours-per-week. Nhng thuc tnh ny c th gip cung cp ng cnh tt hn cho occupation v native-country, bi v mc hc vn, loi hnh cng vic, tui, v s gi lm vic mi tun thng c lin quan mt thit n ngh nghip cng nh quc gia xut x ca mt c nhn.

b. Xy dng m hnh d on gi tr b thiu (da vo mt s ct bit)
In[13]:
# To mt hm  d on gi tr da trn cc thuc tnh quan trng
def impute_missing_values(df_missing, df_not_missing, target_column, reference_columns):
    # in gi tr mode t cc nhm c phn loi theo cc ct lin quan
    for _, row in df_missing.iterrows():
        # To mask cho cc hng trong df_not_missing c cc thuc tnh ging vi hng ang xt ca df_missing
        mask = (df_not_missing[reference_columns] == row[reference_columns].values).all(axis=1)
        
        # Kim tra nu c hng no tha mn mask, nu c, ly gi tr mode t ct target_column
        if df_not_missing[mask].shape[0] > 0:
            df_missing.loc[row.name, target_column] = df_not_missing[mask][target_column].mode()[0]
        else:
            # Nu khng c hng no khp, in mode ca ton b ct
            df_missing.loc[row.name, target_column] = df_not_missing[target_column].mode()[0]

    return df_missing
c. in gi tr b thiu

Ti cho rng cc thuc tnh education,education-num, age, sex, hours-per-week s lin quan n thuc tnh occupation v workclass nn s d on gi tr b thiu 2 thuc tnh ny da trn cc thuc tnh trn.

In[14]:
# in gi tr thiu cho occupation v workclass

occupation_missing = impute_missing_values(occupation_missing, occupation_not_missing, 
                                           'occupation', ['education', 'education-num', 'age', 'sex', 'hours-per-week'])

workclass_missing = impute_missing_values(workclass_missing, workclass_not_missing, 
                                          'workclass', ['education', 'education-num', 'age', 'sex', 'hours-per-week'])

# Gp li d liu  in vi d liu ban u

X.update(occupation_missing)
X.update(workclass_missing)

education_order = {
    "Preschool": 0,
    "1st-4th": 1,
    "5th-6th": 2,
    "7th-8th": 3,
    "9th": 4,
    "10th": 5,
    "11th": 6,
    "12th": 7,
    "HS-grad": 8,
    "Some-college": 9,
    "Assoc-voc": 10,
    "Assoc-acdm": 11,
    "Bachelors": 12,
    "Masters": 13,
    "Prof-school": 14,
    "Doctorate": 15
}

# To hm nh x t t in education_order
def get_education_level(education):
    return education_order.get(education, np.nan)  # tr v np.nan nu khng tm thy trong t in

# p dng hm get_education_level cho ton b ct 'education' vi numpy.vectorize
X['education_level'] = np.vectorize(get_education_level)(X['education'])

def plot_feature_boxplots(data, features, n_rows=3, n_cols=3, figsize=(12, 8)):
    """
    Plots boxplots for specified features from a dataset.

    Parameters:
        data (DataFrame): The dataset containing the features.
        features (list): A list of feature names to plot.
        n_rows (int): Number of rows for the subplot grid. Default is 2.
        n_cols (int): Number of columns for the subplot grid. Default is 3.
        figsize (tuple): Size of the entire figure. Default is (12, 8).
    """
    plt.figure(figsize=figsize)
    
    for i, feature in enumerate(features, 1):
        plt.subplot(n_rows, n_cols, i)
        sns.boxplot(x=data[feature])
        plt.title(f'Boxplot of {feature}')
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

4.1 Xy dng hm chun ho

Min-Max Scaling

$$ X_{\text{scaled}} = \frac{X - X_{\text{min}}}{X_{\text{max}} - X_{\text{min}}} \times (X_{\text{max new}} - X_{\text{min new}}) + X_{\text{min new}} $$

Trong :

  • $X$: gi tr ban u ca feature. -$X_{\text{min}}$: gi tr nh nht ca feature.
  • $X_{\text{max}}$: gi tr ln nht ca feature.
  • $X_{\text{max new}}$ v $X_{\text{min new}}$: khong gi tr mi mong mun sau khi chun ha (thng l ([0, 1])).
In[39]:
# Min-Max Scaling
def min_max_scaling(df, feature, new_min=0, new_max=1):
    X = df[feature].values
    X_min = np.min(X)
    X_max = np.max(X)
    df[feature] = (df[feature] - X_min)/(X_max - X_min) * (new_max - new_min) + new_min
    # X_scaled = (X - X_min) / (X_max - X_min) * (new_max - new_min) + new_min
    # df.loc[:,feature] = X_scaled
    # df.loc[:,feature] = df[feature].astype(float)
    return df

Z-score Standardization:

$$ X_{\text{normalized}} = \frac{X - \mu}{\sigma} $$

Trong :

  • $X$: gi tr ban u ca feature.
  • $\mu$: gi tr trung bnh ca feature.
  • $\sigma $: lch chun ca feature.
In[40]:
def z_score_standardization(df, feature):
    X = df[feature].values
    mean = np.mean(X)
    std = np.std(X)
    if std == 0:
        print(f"Standard deviation is zero for feature: {feature}")
    else:
        df[feature] = (df[feature] - mean)/std
    return df

Robust Scaling

$$ X_{\text{scaled}} = \frac{X - \text{median}(X)}{\text{IQR}(X)} $$

Trong :

  • $X$: gi tr ban u ca feature.
  • $\text{median}(X)$: trung v ca feature.
  • $\text{IQR}(X) = Q_3 - Q_1$: khong t phn v ca feature, vi $ Q_1 $ l phn v th nht (25%) v $Q_3$ l phn v th ba (75%).
In[41]:
# Robust Scaling
def robust_scaling(df, feature):
    X = df[feature].values
    median = np.median(X)
    Q1 = np.percentile(X, 25)
    Q3 = np.percentile(X, 75)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1
    if IQR == 0:
        print(f"IQR is zero for feature: {feature}")
    else:
        df[feature] = (df[feature] - median)/IQR
    return df

5.2 S dng Variance Inflation Factor

Variance Inflation Factor (VIF) l mt ch s c s dng o lng mc a cng tuyn (multicollinearity) gia cc bin c lp trong m hnh hi quy tuyn tnh. a cng tuyn xy ra khi mt hoc nhiu bin c lp c mi quan h qu cht ch vi nhau, iu ny c th lm gim chnh xc v kh nng gii thch ca m hnh.

Nguyn l ca VIF

VIF cho bit mc quan h gia mt bin c lp v cc bin c lp khc trong m hnh. Gi tr VIF cng cao, cng c nhiu a cng tuyn gia bin v cc bin khc, iu ny c th gy ra sai lch trong c lng cc h s ca m hnh.

Cng thc tnh VIF cho mt bin c lp $X_i$ nh sau:

$ \text{VIF}(X_i) = \frac{1}{1 - R^2_i} $

Trong :

  • $R^2_i$ l h s xc nh (R-squared) khi bin c lp $X_i$ c hi quy trn tt c cc bin c lp khc trong m hnh.

Cc bc tnh VIF cho mt bin

  1. Hi quy bin $X_i$ ln cc bin cn li: Hi quy $X_i$ ln tt c cc bin c lp cn li v tnh gi tr $R^2$.

  2. Tnh VIF: S dng cng thc $\text{VIF} = \frac{1}{1 - R^2}$ tnh VIF cho bin $X_i$.

ngha ca VIF

  • VIF = 1: Bin c lp $X_i$ khng c mi quan h tuyn tnh vi cc bin c lp khc. Khng c a cng tuyn, bin ny c lp.

  • 1 < VIF < 5: C mi quan h va phi gia bin $X_i$ v cc bin c lp khc. Mc d c a cng tuyn nh, m hnh vn c th n.

  • VIF > 5 (hoc 10): C s a cng tuyn mnh gia bin $X_i$ v cc bin khc. iu ny c th lm cho m hnh khng n nh v kt qu khng chnh xc. Trong trng hp ny, nn cn nhc loi b hoc kt hp cc bin.

Xy dng hm tnh VIF cho tng ct

In[52]:
# Hm tnh VIF cho tng ct trong X
def calculate_vif(X):
    vif_values = []

    # Duyt qua tng ct trong DataFrame
    for i in range(X.shape[1]):
        # Xc nh cc ct khng phi ct th i
        X_except_i = X.drop(X.columns[i], axis=1)
        target = X.iloc[:, i]

        # Tnh h s hi quy R^2 bng cch s dng hm s t numpy
        coef = np.linalg.lstsq(X_except_i, target, rcond=None)[0]
        predicted = X_except_i @ coef
        r_squared = 1 - (np.sum((target - predicted) ** 2) / np.sum((target - np.mean(target)) ** 2))

        # Kim tra nu r_squared = 1 ( trnh chia cho 0)
        if r_squared == 1:
            vif = np.inf  # t VIF l v cng khi c a cng tuyn hon ton
        else:
            # Tnh VIF cho thuc tnh th i
            vif = 1 / (1 - r_squared)

        vif_values.append(vif)

    return np.array(vif_values)

# S dng ngng VIF (thng l 10)  loi b cc ct c a cng tuyn cao
vif_threshold = 10
# Khi to mt DataFrame cha cc bin
X_selected = X_after_selection_feature.copy()

# Lp li cho n khi khng cn bin no c VIF vt ngng
while True:
    vif_values = calculate_vif(X_selected)  # Tnh VIF cho cc bin hin ti
    max_vif = vif_values.max()  # Tm VIF cao nht

    if max_vif > vif_threshold:
        # Xc nh ct c VIF cao nht v loi b
        max_vif_index = vif_values.argmax()
        column_to_drop = X_selected.columns[max_vif_index]
        print(f"Loi b ct '{column_to_drop}' vi VIF = {max_vif}")
        X_selected = X_selected.drop(columns=[column_to_drop])
    else:
        # Kt thc nu tt c VIF u di ngng
        break
columns_to_keep = X_selected.columns
print("Cc ct c gi li sau khi kim tra VIF:",columns_to_keep)

5.4 Mutual Information

1. Nguyn l ca Mutual Information cho Feature Selection

Mutual Information (MI) o lng mc thng tin m mt thuc tnh (feature) cung cp v nhn mc tiu (target). MI gip xc nh cc thuc tnh c mi quan h ph thuc vi nhn mc tiu. Nhng thuc tnh c MI cao vi nhn mc tiu s cha nhiu thng tin phn bit v thng c ngha hn trong bi ton phn loi.

Cng thc tnh Mutual Information

Mutual Information $ MI(X; Y)$ gia thuc tnh $ X $ v nhn mc tiu $Y$ c tnh bng: $$ MI(X; Y) = H(Y) - H(Y | X) $$

  • $H(Y)$: Entropy ca nhn mc tiu $Y$, o lng s khng chc chn ca $Y$.
  • $H(Y | X)$: Entropy c iu kin ca $ Y $ khi bit gi tr ca $ X $, o lng s khng chc chn cn li ca $ Y $ khi bit $X $.

MI cng ln, thuc tnh $X$ cng cung cp nhiu thng tin v $Y$, v do thng hu ch cho phn loi.

Cng thc tnh Entropy

Entropy $ H(Y) $ ca mt nhn mc tiu $Y $ c tnh bng: $$ H(Y) = - \sum_{i=1}^n P(y_i) \log_2 P(y_i) $$ vi:

  • $P(y_i)$: Xc sut ca tng gi tr c th c ca $Y $.

Entropy c iu kin $H(Y | X)$ c tnh tng t, nhng c iu kin da trn cc gi tr ca $ X $.

2. Gii thut s dng Mutual Information cho vic chn thuc tnh

Di y l cc bc ca gii thut tnh Mutual Information cho mi thuc tnh vi nhn mc tiu trong Jupyter Notebook:

  1. Tnh Entropy ca nhn mc tiu $ Y $:

    • S dng cng thc Entropy tnh $ H(Y) $, o lng mc khng chc chn ca nhn mc tiu.

  2. Tnh Entropy c iu kin cho tng thuc tnh:

    • Vi mi thuc tnh $ X $, tnh ton Entropy c iu kin $ H(Y | X) $. i vi mi gi tr ca $X$, tnh Entropy ca $ Y$ v tnh trung bnh c trng s da trn xc sut xut hin ca mi gi tr trong $ X $.

  3. Tnh Mutual Information:

    • Vi mi thuc tnh $X$, tnh MI bng cng thc $ MI(X; Y) = H(Y) - H(Y | X) $.
    • Lu tr gi tr MI cho tng thuc tnh.

  4. Lc cc thuc tnh:

    • t ngng chn cc thuc tnh c MI ln hn mt gi tr nht nh. Cc thuc tnh c MI cao s gi li cho m hnh phn loi v chng cung cp nhiu thng tin v nhn mc tiu.
In[57]:
# Hm tnh Entropy ca mt thuc tnh
def entropy(y):
    hist = np.bincount(y)
    prob = hist / len(y)
    return -np.sum([p * np.log2(p) for p in prob if p > 0])

# Hm tnh Mutual Information gia tng thuc tnh v nhn mc tiu
def mutual_information(X, target):
    mi = []
    H_y = entropy(target)  # Entropy ca nhn mc tiu
    for i in range(X.shape[1]):
        values, counts = np.unique(X[:, i], return_counts=True)
        H_y_given_x = 0
        for v, c in zip(values, counts):
            H_y_given_x += (c / len(target)) * entropy(target[X[:, i] == v])
        # MI = H(y) - H(y | x)
        mi.append(H_y - H_y_given_x)
    return np.array(mi)

# Chuyn DataFrame sang numpy array v tch ct target
X_values = X_after_selection_feature.values
target = y['is >50K'].values

# Tnh Mutual Information cho tng thuc tnh
mi_scores = mutual_information(X_values, target)

  • Thuc tnh capital-loss:
    - Tng t capital-gain, d liu ca capital-loss c s lch mnh v pha 0 vi mt lng nh gi tr nm pha cao hn.
    $\rightarrow$ dng phng php equal-depth binning x l.

6.2 Xy dng hm binning

In[63]:
# Hm Equal-width Binning
def equal_width_binning(data, num_bins):
    min_val, max_val = np.min(data), np.max(data)
    bins = np.linspace(min_val, max_val, num_bins + 1)  # To ra cc ngng phn chia
    discretized = np.digitize(data, bins) - 1  # t vo cc nhm
    return discretized

# Hm Equal-depth Binning
def equal_depth_binning(data, num_bins):
    quantiles = np.linspace(0, 1, num_bins + 1)
    bins = np.quantile(data, quantiles)  # To cc ngng da trn tn s
    discretized = np.digitize(data, bins, right=True) - 1
    return discretized

6.3 Trc quan ho cc thuc tnh sau khi ri rc ho

In[71]:
# Hm v histogram cho tng thuc tnh vi cc phng php ri rc ha khc nhau
def plot_discretized_histograms(df, columns_width, columns_depth, n_bins=5):
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
    plot_index = 1
    
    # V histogram cho cc ct dng phng php Equal-width Binning
    for column in columns_width:
        # Tnh cc khong gi tr theo Equal-width Binning
        col_min, col_max = df[column].min(), df[column].max()
        bin_width = (col_max - col_min) / n_bins
        equal_width_bins = np.linspace(col_min, col_max, n_bins + 1)
        
        # V histogram cho ct
        plt.subplot(2, 3, plot_index)
        sns.histplot(df[column], bins=equal_width_bins, kde=True, color='skyblue')
        plt.title(f"'{column}' (Equal-width Binning)")
        plt.xlabel(column)
        plt.ylabel("Frequency")
        plt.xticks(equal_width_bins.round(2))  # t ngng gi tr trn trc x
        
        plot_index += 1

    # V histogram cho cc ct dng phng php Equal-depth Binning
    for column in columns_depth:
        # Tnh cc khong gi tr theo Equal-depth Binning
        equal_depth_bins = np.percentile(df[column], np.linspace(0, 100, n_bins + 1))
        
        # V histogram cho ct
        plt.subplot(2, 3, plot_index)
        sns.histplot(df[column], bins=equal_depth_bins, kde=True, color='lightcoral')
        plt.title(f"'{column}' (Equal-depth Binning)")
        plt.xlabel(column)
        plt.ylabel("Frequency")
        plt.xticks(equal_depth_bins.round(2))  # t ngng gi tr trn trc x
        
        plot_index += 1

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# S dng DataFrame X_after_selection_feature  v histogram
columns_width = ['age_discretized', 'fnlwgt_discretized']
columns_depth = ['capital-gain_discretized', 'capital-loss_discretized', 'hours-per-week_discretized']

plot_discretized_histograms(X_after_discretize, columns_width, columns_depth, n_bins=5)
